> This tangy-sweet work-of-art sando makes a great vegetarian lunch or dinner idea. Think
> of tofu as a blank canvas, soaking up all yummy flavors that surround it. Tender
> tofu cubes are dredged and pan-fried until golden, then glazed in a citrusy BBQ
> sauce and sprinkled with spicy pepper jack that melts tantalizingly before your
> eyes. Pile it into a toasted baguette and finish with tangy, crunchy quick-pickled
> onion and jalapeño. Served with crispy roasted potato wedges and garlic-lime mayo
> for dipping, this is one seriously satisfying meal.

== Pickled Veggies ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1} 
(whole onion for 4 servings). Halve @jalapeño{1} lengthwise and remove ribs and seeds 
for less heat, then thinly slice into half-moons. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (for 4, zest 
one lime; quarter both). Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @salt{}, 
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, jalapeño, juice
from half the lime, @sugar{¼%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt.
Microwave until bright pink, ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, tossing occasionally.

== Sauce ==

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{1}, 
@veggie stock concentrate{1}, juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4), and 
@water{¼%cup} (½ cup for 4).

In a third small bowl, combine garlic, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, juice from one lime
wedge (two wedges for 4), a pinch of lime zest, and a pinch of salt and pepper to taste.

== Tofu ==

Pat @tofu{1} dry with #paper towels{}; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick planks. Coat
tofu all over with @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} and season generously with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add tofu and cook until golden brown and crispy, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> You may need to work in batches for 4 servings.

Add BBQ sauce mixture to pan with tofu. Cook, stirring, until tofu is coated and sauce
is thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; sprinkle @pepper jack cheese{½%cup} over tofu and cover with #lid{}.
Set aside until ready to serve.

== Assembly ==

Cut @demi-baguette{2} in half lengthwise. Toast until golden brown. 

> TIP: Place baguettes on a baking sheet or toast directly on oven rack. Brush cut
> sides with melted butter first for extra richness.

Fill baguettes with cheesy BBQ tofu (spooning any remaining sauce from pan over top)
and as much pickled onion and jalapeño (draining first) as you like.

Divide sandwiches between plates. Serve with potato wedges and garlic-lime mayo for
dipping.